\begin{frame}{Modern Portfolio Theory:International}
Much is the same when the portfolio theory applied to international asset management
\pause
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item The \emph{investment universe} becomes the whole world rather than one specific country
\item The \emph{market portfolio} is all the assets in the world
\item Questions about asset and industry allocation are combined with those of region or country
\item The structure of the asset management industry tends towards specialisation and fragmentation
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\section{Home Bias}
\begin{frame}{Home bias}
	French and Poterba (1991) find home bias in equity investment
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
		\pause
	\item Lower risk can be achieved for same return with the use of international diversification
	\item It is a result that has been repeated many times
		\begin{itemize}
				\item Coeurbacier and Rey (2011)
				\item Mishra (2012)
				\item Berger and Warnock (2003)
				\item Polwitoon and Tawatnuntachai (2006)
		\end{itemize}
	\item Across asset classes
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

